If I understand what you want to do, you can use `ChangeType` by using a generic method with `IConvertible ` constraint.

It will take two parameters:

- The string to convert,
- The data value to change as `out`.

So we use a simple `try - ChangeType - catch` to do the operation.

```
/// &lt;summary&gt;
/// Get a value from a string and return true if success
/// else return false if not convertible
/// &lt;/summary&gt;
/// &lt;typeparam name=&quot;T&quot;&gt;The generic type parameter&lt;/typeparam&gt;
/// &lt;param name=&quot;str&quot;&gt;The string to convert&lt;/param&gt;
/// &lt;param name=&quot;value&quot;&gt;The value to get&lt;/param&gt;
/// &lt;returns&gt;The converted value if success else the default of the type&lt;/returns&gt;
public bool GetValueFromString&lt;T&gt;(string str, out T value)
  where T : IConvertible
{
  try
  {
    value = (T)Convert.ChangeType(str, typeof(T));
    return true;
  }
  catch
  {
    value = default(T);
    return false;
  }
}
```

